  "description": [
    "SS Seth od Be BENGAL HURKARU K SS ie a BENGAL HURKARU CALCUTTA MONDAY MAY 3 1819 The Kedgeree report of Saturday was blank as to arrivalsthat of yesterday informs us that the Ganges Captain Falconer and the Dutch brig Marta Captain Eders have entered the river m The Ganges is from Bombay which she left on Mm the 10th March the Maria is from Ghent but j has most probably made some stay at some inter mediate ports as the date of ber departure from that place is so far back as the 5th of August i Nothing new except what might have occurred on their passages can be expected from either Our Madras papers reaching to the 15th April Mm state the arrrival there of the Phaeton Captain M Dillon on the i1th ultimo The packets to be senton 4er to England were to be closed on the 116th The Mermaid Captain Hammond from Calcutta anchored in Madras Roads on the 10th April The packet ship Ajax sailed for the Cape Mm and England on the 11th ditto is His Majestys 25th Dragoons had embarked on W the Manglesand Belle Alliance Six troops had f sailed for England"
